HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language. It is the standard language used to create and design web pages by defining the structure of content on the web.

1.HTML 1.0 (1991)
  First version by Tim Berners-Lee
  Basic structure and text formatting only
2.HTML 2.0 (1995)
  Standardized by IETF
  Added forms, tables, and more tags
3.HTML 3.2 (1997)
  W3C standard
  Added fonts, colors, scripting (JavaScript), applets
4.HTML 4.01 (1999)
  Introduced CSS support
  Separation of content and design
  Deprecated some older tags
5.XHTML 1.0 (2000)
  HTML with strict XML syntax
  Ensured better compatibility
6.HTML5 (2014)
  Modern standard
  Added semantic tags (<header>, <footer>), multimedia (<audio>, <video>), canvas, local storage, and APIs for web apps
